=== Running the Tutorials ===

R4E provides 3 different ways to perform reviews:  Basic, Informal and Formal Review Types.  They will all be demonstrated in the tutorials below. Here's a brief description of each Review Type:

*[[#Basic and Informal Reviews workflows|Basic Reviews]]:  Basic Reviews do not use phases, anomalies written are stateless, and participant do not assume any roles.  These are used to do quick, small reviews.

*[[#Basic and Informal Reviews workflows|Informal Reviews]]: Informal Reviews do not use phases.  However anomalies written are stateful and their states can be tracked as the review progresses and they can be postponed to be eventually fixed in other reviews. All anomalies should be set to a terminal state before the review can be completed.  Participants have roles assigned to them.  Informal Reviews are typically used to do agile reviews.

*[[#Formal Review workflow|Formal Reviews]]: Formal Reviews are based on the IEEE Standard for Software Reviews (IEEE Std 1028-1997) standard.  They are divided into multiple phases (Planning, Preparation, Decision, Rework), and criterias should be met before transitioning from a review phase to another. As in Informal Reviews, the anomalies written are stateful, could be postponed, and ultimately need to be set to a terminal state before the review could be completed.  Formal Reviews are typically used in organizations that require a more organized review process.

For more information, please refer to the [[#Concepts]] section below.

